main event: A metallic object was observed at the rear of a paint and hardware store in Melbourne, Florida on August 17, 1960.
interesting points: The object was approximately 2 to 3 feet long and 18 inches wide,It appeared to be made of metal and was shaped in an irregular fashion,The object was located near the rear of the building, partially obscured from view,There were no markings or obvious identification on the object,Local authorities were unable to determine its nature or source.
witness description: no identifiable individuals present in the report
